### 1. Create a user (Required because the POST /api/blogs route needs at least one user in the DB)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "root",
  "name": "Superuser",
  "password": "password"
}

### 2. Create a new blog (This will automatically link to the user created above)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/blogs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Understanding Mongoose Populate",
  "author": "Jane Doe",
  "url": "https://example.com/mongoose-populate",
  "likes": 12
}

### 3. Fetch all blogs (Verify the 'user' field is a populated object, not just an ID)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/blogs

### 4. Fetch all users (Verify the 'blogs' array contains populated blog objects)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/users

### Login to get token
POST http://localhost:3001/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "root",
  "password": "password"
}

